						               													<description>Combat Command: The Bulge to Berlin adds army lists for the forces of the USSR, the British Commonwealth, Germany and the United States for the final months of the war in northern Europe for Combat Command and other similar platoon level games.  &amp;#10;The module covers the period between December 1944 through the surrender of Germany in May 1945.  &amp;#10;All the combatants major armor and infantry organizations are covered as well as Germany's ad hoc last defender battle groups.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;It also provides rules for converting historical research for battles fought in this period into a balanced game as well as methods for setting up hypothetical battles between two evenly matched forces.  A full terrain generation system is included.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Besides the orders of battle the module also includes an historical scenario, the Battle of Rodt, which illustrates how to create historical battles using this module.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
